<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
	course-materials.ptx
	Homepage section giving students one place to reach the other
	deployed course materials (today: the guided lecture notes).

	Why links instead of folding the worksheets into this article:
	the notes are a separate PreTeXt document (source/notes.ptx) that
	builds three ways from one source - web-stu / web-key (HTML) and
	pdf-key (print) - via the <version include> component filtering in
	publication/publication-stu.ptx / publication/publication-key.ptx.
	The homepage builds once, with publication/homepage-pub.ptx, whose
	<version include="html"/> lists neither
	the "stu" nor the "key" component, and a PreTeXt <article> cannot
	contain a <chapter> anyway.  Embedding the worksheets here would
	therefore require converting the homepage to a <book> AND splitting
	it into parallel student/instructor homepage targets (two homepage
	URLs), while orphaning the pdf-key target.  Linking keeps one
	homepage and preserves the student/instructor split.
	TODO(geoff): if you would rather have the worksheets rendered inside
	the homepage document itself despite the above (one merged document,
	built twice), say the word and it can be restaged that way.

	The relative hrefs below mirror the deploy-dir attributes in
	project.ptx (notes-student, notes-instructor) and the cards in
	site/index.html - keep all three in sync.  They resolve on the
	deployed GitHub Pages site (each target is a sibling directory of
	homepage/), not in a local output/ preview.
-->
<section xml:id="course-materials" label="course-materials">
	<title>Course Materials</title>

	<introduction>
		<p>
			All materials for MA 301 are published on this site and are updated
			as the semester progresses. Bookmark the pages you use most.
		</p>
	</introduction>

	<subsection xml:id="materials-guided-notes" label="materials-guided-notes">
		<title>Guided Lecture Notes</title>

		<p>
			Class meetings are built around <term>guided lecture notes</term>:
			one worksheet per meeting, with definitions, examples, and blanks
			that we complete together during class. Bring the day's worksheet
			(printed or on a device you can write on) to every meeting.
		</p>

		<!-- Links live in the item bodies, not the <title>s: PreTeXt
		     silently strips <url> markup inside a <dl> item title. -->
		<p>
			<dl>
				<li>
					<title>Student Edition</title>
					<p>
						<url href="../notes-student/">Open the Student Edition</url>
						<mdash/> the working copy: statements and blanks, no
						answers. This is the version to bring to class.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<title>Instructor Key</title>
					<p>
						<url href="../notes-instructor/">Open the Instructor Key</url>
						<mdash/> the same worksheets with the blanks filled and
						solutions revealed. Posted for checking your work
						<em>after</em> we cover the material in class.
					</p>
				</li>
			</dl>
		</p>
	</subsection>

	<!-- Coursebook card: mirror of the disabled card in site/index.html.
	     Re-enable this subsection together with the deploy-dir="book"
	     attribute in project.ptx and the site/index.html card once the
	     book target is marked for deploy (see the note in project.ptx).
	<subsection xml:id="materials-coursebook" label="materials-coursebook">
		<title>Coursebook</title>
		<p>
			The course textbook, adapted from <em>APEX Calculus</em>
			(CC BY-NC 4.0): <url href="../book/">Coursebook</url>.
		</p>
	</subsection>
	-->
</section>
